<section xml:id="C25.S8">
<title>Sums</title>          
<para xml:id="C25.S8.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="1" xml:id="C25.S8.p1.s1">
 <Math equation-number="25.8.1" mode="display" xml:id="C25.S8.E1">\sum_{k=2}^{\infty}\left(\zeta\left(k\right)-1\right)=1</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="2" xml:id="C25.S8.p1.s2">
<Math equation-number="25.8.2" mode="display" xml:id="C25.S8.E2">\sum_{k=0}^{\infty}\frac{\Gamma\left(s+k\right)}{(k+1)!}\left(\zeta\left(s+k \right)-1\right)=\Gamma\left(s-1\right), if s\neq 1,0,-1,-2,\dots</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="3" sentence-num-in-section="3" xml:id="C25.S8.p1.s3">
<Math equation-number="25.8.3" mode="display" xml:id="C25.S8.E3">\sum_{k=0}^{\infty}\frac{{\left(s\right)_{k}}\zeta\left(s+k\right)}{k!2^{s+k}} =(1-2^{-s})\zeta\left(s\right), if s\neq 1</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="4" sentence-num-in-section="4" xml:id="C25.S8.p1.s4">
<Math equation-number="25.8.4" mode="display" xml:id="C25.S8.E4">\sum_{k=1}^{\infty}\frac{(-1)^{k}}{k}(\zeta\left(nk\right)-1)=\ln\left(\prod_{ j=0}^{n-1}\Gamma\left(2-e^{(2j+1)\pi i/n}\right)\right), if n=2,3,4,\dots</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="5" sentence-num-in-section="5" xml:id="C25.S8.p1.s5">
<Math equation-number="25.8.5" mode="display" xml:id="C25.S8.E5">\sum_{k=2}^{\infty}\zeta\left(k\right)z^{k}=-\gamma z-z\psi\left(1-z\right), if |z|&lt;1</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="6" sentence-num-in-section="6" xml:id="C25.S8.p1.s6">
<Math equation-number="25.8.6" mode="display" xml:id="C25.S8.E6">\sum_{k=0}^{\infty}\zeta\left(2k\right)z^{2k}=-\tfrac{1}{2}\pi z\cot\left(\pi z \right), if |z|&lt;1</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="7" sentence-num-in-section="7" xml:id="C25.S8.p1.s7">
<Math equation-number="25.8.7" mode="display" xml:id="C25.S8.E7">\sum_{k=2}^{\infty}\frac{\zeta\left(k\right)}{k}z^{k}=-\gamma z+\ln\Gamma\left (1-z\right), if |z|&lt;1</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="8" sentence-num-in-section="8" xml:id="C25.S8.p1.s8">
<Math equation-number="25.8.8" mode="display" xml:id="C25.S8.E8">\sum_{k=1}^{\infty}\frac{\zeta\left(2k\right)}{k}z^{2k}=\ln\left(\frac{\pi z}{ \sin\left(\pi z\right)}\right), if |z|&lt;1</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="9" sentence-num-in-section="9" xml:id="C25.S8.p1.s9">
<Math equation-number="25.8.9" mode="display" xml:id="C25.S8.E9">\sum_{k=1}^{\infty}\frac{\zeta\left(2k\right)}{(2k+1)2^{2k}}=\frac{1}{2}-\frac {1}{2}\ln 2.</Math>
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="10" sentence-num-in-section="10" xml:id="C25.S8.p1.s10">
 <Math equation-number="25.8.10" mode="display" xml:id="C25.S8.E10">\sum_{k=1}^{\infty}\frac{\zeta\left(2k\right)}{(2k+1)(2k+2)2^{2k}}=\frac{1}{4} -\frac{7}{4\pi^{2}}\zeta\left(3\right)</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
<para xml:id="C25.S8.p2">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="11" xml:id="C25.S8.p2.s1">
For other sums see Prudnikov et al. (1986b, pp. 648–649),Hansen (1975, pp. 355–357), Ogreid and Osland (1998), andSrivastava and Choi (2001, Chapter 3).
</sentence>

</para>
 
